title: Grateful Dead Live at Red Rocks Ampitheatre on 1982-07-28
lineage: Cassette Master (Nakamichi DR-1/Dolby B) -> Sound Devices 744T (24bit/96k) -> Adobe Audition v1.5 -> Samplitude Professional v10.22 -> FLAC/16
description:
Set 1

Shakedown Street, Beat It On Down The Line-> Greatest Story Ever Told, They Love Each Other, Mama Tried-> Mexicali Blues, Big Railroad Blues, Lazy Lightning-> Supplication-> Deal

Set 2

Women Are Smarter, Althea, Let It Grow-> He's Gone-> Truckin'-> Drums-> Spanish Jam-> Not Fade Away-> Black Peter-> Sugar Magnolia, E: It's All Over Now Baby Blue

reviews.review_text:
Level Good old fashioned chatter before Shakedown 
God Damn it Wise Dont Fuckin touch my levels
smokin show maybe it doesnt compete with the night before, but check this one out for sure.. very nice playing
On further thought Totally great 2nd set. Adventurous and spidery playing all over the place. Let It Grow is an absolute monster even with bob's vocal hiccup. New transfers sound incredible.
This is smokin! I know that term is cliche. I really just wanted to say that the taper getting pissed at the idiot was the best part of this for me.
Damnit, Wise...! Fantastic show. Airy, soft but clear recording.

Something's missing! Between "Women" and "Althea", Weir says "Welcome to the Annual Red Rocks Rainout but we're still here." 

Seems as though all 3 copies of this on IA have that edited out.

Rockin at Red Rocks I listened to the show over the course of a week or so and it was really enjoyable.  Great setlist featuring some unusual placements.  Recording/sound quality A+.  Boys definitely still brought it in '82!

Rumor I recall a rumor going around before the show that they were going to do Stephen. So during space and Spanish Jam we listened and on every tape you can hear us notice the begining tease. If thee were a roof to red rocks sure would of been blown if they did it. Gets 5 stars because sound is very good and show was even better.   I too had the tape with this is the annual red rocks rain out before Women? or althea?
Top Notch 82 Highlights: Let It Grow, He's Gone, Truckin', Drums, Spanish Jam, Black Peter
